snippet.textDisplay:
TIPS

1. Get a good night sleep
2. Make your bed
3. Avoid checking your phone after waking up
4. Create a morning ritual
5. Get ready
6. Wear work outfits that aren’t too uncomfortable
7. Create a distinct workspace (desk as far away from bed as possible)
8. Clear away clutter
9. Clear out your digital workspace
10. Write to do lists and break down different tasks into smaller steps - doesn’t lead to procrastination
11. Avoid distractions
12. Create rules you have to follow when sitting at your desk
13. Shut off your phone
14. Productive breaks - physical activities like cleaning etc.
15. Switch tasks
16. Make plans to look forward to in the evening

snippet.textDisplay: hi! If you see this, you should try a portuguese-made notebook called InfiteBook, it works similar to a white board but is shaped like a notebook, so you can use the pages, digitalize them into an app if necessary and then erase it and use it again. I've been using it and it works quite well, it's eco-friendly and not so expensive since you don't need to buy other notebooks and it lives for a infinite number of them. You can check out the website https://www.infinitebook.com/. I thought of this when I saw you using that cheap notebook, instead of writing to do lists there and never look at them again, you can write them on this notebook and erase them when finished. Give it a try, you have various models and colors. Keep up the good work!
